Usage: catalyst [options] [command]

Command Line Tool for CATALYST

Options:
  -v, --version                                              Print the Catalyst CLI version number
  -p, --project <name|project_id>                            Specify the Catalyst project to be used for a command
  --token <token>                                            Supply an authentication token for a command
  --dc <us|eu|in|au>                                         Supply a data center for a command
  --org <org_id>                                             Supply a Org ID to be used for a command
  --verbose                                                  Change the log level to verbose for debugging purposes
  -h, --help                                                 Display help for a Catalyst command

Commands:
  login [options]                                            Log the CLI in to your Catalyst account
  logout                                                     Log the CLI out of your Catalyst account
  whoami                                                     Print the email address of the user currently logged in
  token:generate [options]                                   Generate a token to authenticate accessing the CLI from a remote     
                                                             system
  token:list                                                 List all the available tokens generated in this CLI
  token:revoke <id>                                          Revoke a token generated in this CLI
  project:list                                               List all the Catalyst projects you have access to
  project:use [name_or_project_id]                           Set an active Catalyst project for your working directory
  project:reset                                              Clear an active project selection and reset to the base project      
  init [options] [feature]                                   Initialize a Catalyst project, function, and client resources in the 
                                                             local directory
  iac:pack [zip_name]                                        Creates a import ready zip file
  iac:import [options] [file_path]                           Deploy the iac zip file to console and create a new project with it. 
  iac:export [options]                                       Create a zip file out of existing project in console
  iac:status [options] <operation>                           Displays the status of iac schedule progress
  codelib:install [options] [git-url]                        Install the code library functionalities into your project
  client:setup                                               Set up and configure the client directory in your project directory  
  client:delete [options] [client_version]                   Delete a version of the client from the remote console or the local  
                                                             directory
  functions:setup                                            Set up and configure the function directory in your project
                                                             directory
  functions:add                                              Add a function of the required stack to the function directory       
  functions:delete [options] [function_name_or_id]           Delete a function from the remote console or the local directory     
  functions:shell [options]                                  Launch a node shell to test emulated functions of any stack or type, 
                                                             other than Advanced I/O functions
  functions:execute [options] [function_name] [data]         Execute the Non-Http functions
  functions:config [options] [function_name_or_id]           Perform advanced configurations such as memory allocation on a       
                                                             function in your project
  appsail:add                                                Link an already existing AppSail to Catalyst Project
  slate:link [options]                                       Links an existing local application to the Catalyst Slate service    
                                                             for web hosting
  slate:create [options]                                     Generates a new Slate app with starter examples
  slate:unlink [options]                                     Removes the linked Slate configuration from the local app
  serve [options]                                            Serve Basic I/O and Advanced I/O functions, Appsail and the client,  
                                                             to test them locally
  run-script|run [command]                                   Run a particular command script defined in catalyst.json
  pull [feature]                                             Pull resources of your project from the remote console to the local  
                                                             directory
  deploy [options]                                           Deploy the Catalyst project and project resources to the Catalyst    
                                                             development environment from the local directory
  event:generate|generate:event [options] <source> <action>  Generate sample payloads from different components or custom event   
                                                             sources to test Event functions
  event:generate:integ [options] <service>                   Generate sample payloads for the required integration service to     
                                                             test Integration functions
  event:generate:job [jobpool_id]                            Generate sample payloads for job functions
  signals:generate <publisher_service> <event_name>          Generate sample payloads from different components or custom event   
                                                             publishers to test Event functions
  config:set <key=value>                                     Set catalyst configuration as a key value pair
  config:get <key>                                           Get catalyst config value for the specified key
  config:delete <key>                                        Delete a key from catalyst config
  config:list                                                List all your catalyst configurations
  apig:status [options]                                      Obtain the current status of API Gateway for your project and the    
                                                             schedule progress
  apig:enable                                                Enable API Gateway for your project
  apig:disable                                               Disable API Gateway for your project
  ds:import [options] [file]                                 Bulk write records to a table in the Catalyst Data Store
  ds:export [options] [table]                                Bulk read records from a table in the Catalyst Data Store
  ds:status [options] <operation> [jobid]                    Display the job status of a Data Store import or export operation    
  help [command]                                             Display help information
